22. Q. Pedio : Q. Pedius was Caesar’s lieutenant in Gaul in 58 B.c. ; in 49 praetor ; in 45 was again Caesar’s lieutenant in Spain, and took a prominent part in the repulse of the Pom- peian party there.

A. Plotius in 51 B.o., after his aedileship, was praetor urbanus (ad Act. 5. 15. 1) and friend of T. Antistius, quaestor of Macedonia. In 48 B.c. he was propraetor of Pontus and Bithynia.
